Sokode ashi o kitte ugokenaku suru

Soshite, yasei no shinzou o eguri dasu noda

snippet.description:
KRAMP Teaser on Hasya Movies.

KRAMP is an Upcoming 2025 Telugu Movie Starring Kiran Abbavaraam, Yukti Thareja & Others. Directed by Jains Nani. Music by Chaitan Bharadwaj. Produced by Razesh Danda under Hasya Movies Banner and Shiva Bommak under Ruudransh Celluloid. The film is set to release in theaters this Diwali on October 18, 2025.

snippet.title: India vs Pakistan, 14th T20 Match Cricket Live Commentary | IND Vs PAK Asia Cup 2025 | IND BAT
snippet.description:
India vs Pakistan, 14th T20 Match Cricket Live Commentary | IND Vs PAK Asia Cup 2025 | Live Match, IND BAT

For Contact umerhafeez2022@gmail.com 

Topics to be covered in the live stream üëáüèªüëáüèªüëáüèªüëáüèª

India vs Pakistan live Match
IND vs PAK live
IND vs PAK live match today 
Live Cricket Match Today 
Cricket Live 
Asia Cup Live 
Asia Cup 2025 Live
Live Match 

When: September 21, 06:30 PM LOCAL / 8:00 PM IST

Venue üëáüèª
India vs Pakistan live Match Dubai,
Where: Dubai International Stadium

What to expect: India vs Pakistan Asia Cup 2025, 14th Match. Earlier the 6th match of the Asia Cup was played between Pakistan vs India, India won by 7 wickets against Pakistan. If we look at pitch, another slow, dry surface, with equal boundaries on both sides and a thin grass cover to hold it together. It's likely the same center pitch used for the last India-Pakistan game. Suryakumar believes conditions here haven't shifted much across innings, unlike in Abu Dhabi where dew played a hand. Toss hasn't had a decisive say at this venue. The temperatures are forecast to be around 35 degrees around match start but the evenings in the city are already cooler than a week ago.

Team news:

India

After giving all batters and part-timers a run against Oman, India are set to revert to full strength, bringing back Jasprit Bumrah and Varun Chakaravarthy. Varun was among the few to train on match eve, practicing his scrambled seam legbreaks and googlies against a set of stumps. The others at the training were Shubman Gill and Abhishek Sharma, who bowled and batted and will be a key figure once again.

Injuries/Unavailability: Axar Patel, who struck his head while fielding in Abu Dhabi, is understood to be fine and available. No cover has been called.

Tactics & matchups: Samson and Tilak struggled against spin in Abu Dhabi, going 22 balls without a boundary. Their face-off with Abrar Ahmed will be crucial. The legspinner has bowled 70 balls in this Asia Cup and conceded just two boundaries.

Probable XI: Abhishek Sharma, Shubman Gill, Suryakumar Yadav(c), Tilak Varma, Sanju Samson(w), Shivam Dube, Hardik Pandya, Axar Patel, Kuldeep Yadav, Jasprit Bumrah, Varun Chakaravarthy

Pakistan

Against UAE, Pakistan recalled Haris Rauf and Khushdil Shah, leaving out Sufiyan Muqeem and Faheem Ashraf. That balance is expected to continue. Eyes will be on Saim Ayub, on a hat-trick of ducks, and Hasan Nawaz, who needs runs.

Injuries/Unavailability: No reported injuries since their last match.

Tactics & matchups: Kuldeep Yadav's record against Pakistan looms again. Fakhar Zaman (30 runs, 3 dismissals in 35 balls) and Salman Agha (6 runs, 2 dismissals in 12 balls) have both found him tough across formats.

Probable XI: Saim Ayub, Sahibzada Farhan, Mohammad Haris(w), Fakhar Zaman, Salman Agha(c), Khushdil Shah, Hasan Nawaz, Mohammad Nawaz, Shaheen Afridi, Haris Rauf, Abrar Ahmed

snippet.title: Vrusshabha Official Teaser | Mohanlal as a King | Directed by Nanda Kishore | Diwali 2025 Release
snippet.description:
#Vrusshabha #Mohanlal #Diwali2025 #VrusshabhaTeaser #RoarOfVrusshabha #ConnekktMedia #BalajiTelefilms #AbishekSVyasStudios #AashirvadCinemas

Welcome to the World of Vrusshabha.

A unique story brought to life through an unforgettable cinematic experience for global audiences. With Mohanlal playing a king for the very first time in a bilingual epic, Vrusshabha is a film that promises to stay with you long after you leave the theatre. Vrusshabha is a grand Pan Indian film shot simultaneously in Malayalam and Telugu, and dubbed in Hindi and Kannada.


Starring: Mohanlal, Samarjit Lankesh, Ragini Dwivedi

Crew:
Written and Directed by Nanda Kishore & Team

Presented by Connekkt Media and Balaji Telefilms in association with Abishek S Vyas Studios,
Produced by Shobha Kapoor, Ektaa R. Kapoor, C.K. Padma Kumar, Varun Mathur, Saurabh Mishra, Abishek S. Vyas, Praveer Singh, Vishal Gurnani, Juhi Parekh Mehta
Group CEO & CFO (BTL) : Sanjay Dwivedi 
Dialogues : SRK, Janardhan Maharshi, Karthik 
Music : Sam CS
Director of Photography : Antony Samson
Editor : K.M. Prakash
Sound Designers : Resul Pookutty (CAS, MPSE), Vijay Kumar (MPSE)
Co-Director : Shailendra Kumar K J
Associate Producer (BTL) : Janvi Gill
Group Head ‚Äì Commercial & Administration (BTL) : Hamavvand D. Chawda
Supervising Producer (BTL) : Shrey Jhawar
Production Designers : Nanditha Singh, Mohan B. Kere Action Directors : Peter Hein, Stunt Silva, Nikhil Costume Stylist : Harini Ramakrishna
Choreography : Kruti Mahesh
Re-Recording & Mix : Sarath Mohan
DI : Primefocus Ltd
Colorist : Andreas Brueckl (Andy)
Post Production Head (BTL) : Manohar Pandya
Makeup Chief : Jagdish Yera
VFX Supervisors : Chetan & Kevin
VFX : Animantra VFX
Direction Department : Naresh Babu, Bharath Shivaraju, Ajay Shrinivas, Raghuraj Gowda
Assistant Editor : Rudresh Lake
Group Marketing Head (Connekkt Media) : Manan Shah Marketing Director : Deepak Sahu (ND Media Works) Post Supervisor : Abhishek Matai
Visual Promotions : Mahesh S Reddy

snippet.title: Live: IND vs PAK, Asia Cup 2025, Live Cricket Match Today, Cricket Live, India vs Pakistan Live
snippet.description:
Live: IND vs PAK, Asia Cup 2025, Live Cricket Match Today, Cricket Live, India vs Pakistan Live

For queries, you can email us at: mohsinali51066@gmail.com

1ST INNINGS PREVIEW:
Brilliant batting from Pakistan and equally bad fielding display from India, see the Men in Green post a formidable total of 171/5 in 20 overs after being sent in. Sahibzada Farhan was dropped by Abhishek Sharama in the first over and he didn't look back after that, taking on every bowler and smashing the ball to all parts of the Dubai International Stadium. A last ball six from Faheem Ashraf gives Pakistan the momentum at the halfway mark in this contest. This is also Pakistan's highest total against India batting first. The last time they crossed the 150-mark was back in 2022 at the MCG.

Earlier in the game, India won the toss and invited Pakistan to bat first under hot and humid conditions in Dubai. The Men in Green went with a changed opening pair as Fakhar Zaman replaced Saim Ayub to partner Sahibzada Farhan.

Abhishek Sharma dropped Farhan when he was on nought and he made India pay big time, scoring a quick-fire half-century. 

The opening pair put the pressure straightaway on Jasprit Bumrah and went after him from the word go. Hardik Pandya broke the opening stand by sending back Fakhar with an off-cutter.

Saim Ayub walked in at 3 and gave Farhan nice company as the duo kept the scoreboard ticking and put the bad balls away. They added 72 runs for the second wicket before Ayub fell for 21.

Farhan perished for 58. Mohammad Nawaz then took the onus on himself to move the scoreboard. Captain Salman Ali Agha remained not out on 17 off 13 but the cameo from Faheem Ashraf, who made 20 off 8 took Pakistan past the 170-run mark.

Bumrah was off colour tonight, he gave away 45 runs and failed to pick any wickets in his four overs. Shivam Dube was the unlikely hero with the ball for India, bowling four overs. He went for 33 and picked up 2 wickets. Kuldeep Yadav and Hardik Pandya were the other bowlers who got a wicket.

Pakistan XI:

snippet.title: Jeet Ka Junoon | Official TEZ FFMIC Anthem ft. @KDYadav23  | Free Fire MAX India Cup 2025
snippet.description:
The wait is over ‚Äì presenting ‚ÄúJeet Ka Junoon‚Äù, the official anthem of the TEZ Free Fire MAX India Cup 2025! üé∂

This anthem captures the grit, grind, and unstoppable spirit of India‚Äôs finest Free Fire MAX warriors. From long nights of struggle to the glory of the Grand Finals, it‚Äôs all about one thing ‚Äì the Junoon to Win! üí™üî•

And leading the charge is none other than Indian Cricket star Kuldeep Yadav, inspiring the next generation of champions to chase their dreams. üèÜ

üéß Witness the anthem.
